# RogueAsteroid Project Rules

## Project Type
- Python-based Asteroids Clone
- Designer (User) / Engineer (AI) Collaboration

## Core Rules
1. Check DEVELOPMENT_LOG.md first when resuming
2. Follow design-first approach
3. Engineer implements only approved designs
4. All changes documented in real-time
5. Use DRY, SOLID, and KISS principles
6. Use PEP8 for Python code
7. Use PEP257 for docstrings
8. Preserve existing code unless:
   - It violates current design patterns
   - It causes compatibility issues
   - It has been explicitly marked for replacement
   - It has been superseded by new functionality

## Documentation
- PROJECT_CHARTER.md: Roles and methodology
- GAME_DESIGN_DOCUMENT.md: Game specifications
- DEVELOPMENT_LOG.md: Progress and tasks
=> All documentation in docs/
   - Runtime logs in docs/logs/runtime/
   - Debug logs in docs/logs/debug/
   - Design docs in docs/design/
   - API docs in docs/api/

## Version Control
- Use [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] format (24-hour time)
- Use category tags:
  [DESIGN]   - Design decisions and changes
  [IMPL]     - Implementation of new features
  [TEST]     - Testing related changes
  [TASK]     - General development tasks
  [BUG]      - Bug reports and tracking
  [FIX]      - Bug fixes and corrections
  [NOTE]     - General notes and documentation
  [REVIEW]   - Code review and feedback
  [PERF]     - Performance improvements
  [REFACTOR] - Code restructuring
  [CONFIG]   - Configuration changes 